US FDA MEETING ON TOXOPLASMA AND BORRELIA SERODIAGNOSTIC KITS
=============================================================
The FDA [U.S. Food & Drug Administration] Microbiology Devices
Panel of the Medical Devices Advisory Committee will meet on
January 26, 1996 to discuss issues concerning the accuracy
of commercially available serological kits for the detection
of human anti-Toxoplasma IgM and anti-Borrelia burgdorferi
(etiological agent of Lyme Disease) antibodies in
relation to their indication for use. The meeting will be held at
the Gaithersburg Hilton, Grand Ballroom, 620 Perry Pkwy.,
Gaithersburg, MD and will start at 9:45 am. The first hour is
allotted to an open public hearing. Additional information may be
obtained from Freddie M. Poole at 301-594-2096. Notice of this
meeting has been published in the Federal Register Notices, Friday
December 29, 1995.

Gaithersburg is approximately 20 miles north of Washington, DC.

--
Roxanne G. Shively
Tel.: (301) 594-2096; fax 594-5941"
e-mail: RGS@FDADR.CDRH.FDA.GOV
